OL,6,FDescribing her time as a teenager with
OL,7,Falopecia, Emma said: "It was very
OL,8,Fhidden. I didn't want to talk about
OL,9,Fit. I didn't want anyone to know.
OL,11,F"And I was quite shy at school. I was
OL,12,Fkind of suppressing it and not not
OL,13,Ftalking about it or I didn't like
OL,14,Fanyone to look at my hair quite often
OL,15,Fwhen you got your hair, you'd see
OL,16,Fpeople looking at the top of your
OL,17,Fforehead and it would be like, oh,
OL,18,Fstop looking, stop looking."
